dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Major and minor hydrological features (rivers, lakes, streams and ditches) compiled for a planimetric basemap. Data extents cover Kent's city limits and surrounding area. Names are in the TAG field. Type of feature is in the TYPE_S field and CAT = 2 will display important stream features.

Horizontal accuracy is generally +/- 10 feet.

Compiled from 1988 aerial photography using photogrammetric methods under a contract with Roy F. Weston.
Coverage has been continuously updated since it was created by Kent GIS staff using site plans and ortho photography.
